# Fudi Agent Routing

When working on Fudi, route tasks to the correct specialist by reading their definition from `.agents/`:

| Task Type | Agent File | Temperature |
|-----------|-----------|-------------|
| Architecture / Clean Architecture | `.agents/architect.md` | 0.1 |
| Database schema / RLS / migrations | `.agents/database-architect.md` | 0.1 |
| UI screens / states / accessibility | `.agents/ux-ui.md` | 0.45 |
| Business rules / state machines / permissions | `.agents/business-logic.md` | 0.15 |
| Testing / TDD / coverage | `.agents/test-engineer.md` | 0.1 |
| A11y / Sentry / error hierarchy / breadcrumbs | `.agents/accessibility-observability.md` | 0.1 |
| External integrations / contracts / fallbacks | `.agents/integrations.md` | 0.15 |
| Deployment / CI-CD / flavors / secrets | `.agents/deployment-sre.md` | 0.1 |
| ADRs / changelog / documentation | `.agents/technical-documentation.md` | 0.1 |
| React→Flutter migration / mockup extraction | `.agents/migration-specialist.md` | 0.2 |
| Design tokens / components / theme | `.agents/component-library.md` | 0.3 |
| Rendering / memory / animations optimization | `.agents/performance.md` | 0.1 |
| Auth / secure storage / OWASP / GDPR / PCI | `.agents/security-compliance.md` | 0.1 |
| Funnels / metrics / A/B testing / events | `.agents/analytics-growth.md` | 0.2 |
| MercadoPago / webhooks / refunds / split | `.agents/payments.md` | 0.1 |
| Multi-task coordination / feature priority | `.agents/fudi-orchestrator.md` | 0.2 |

## How to Use

1. Read the relevant `.agents/<name>.md` file BEFORE writing code
2. Follow the agent's protocol and constraints
3. When multiple agents are needed, start with the primary and consult secondary
4. Always validate against Fase 1 restrictions (pickup-only, no cart, no delivery)
5. Reference `AGENTS.md` for behavioral rules and `docs/ai/` for domain knowledge
